{
  "stem": "22869.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She came back to the city that they had taken her from, and she begins going around telling people of the mass murder that's going on in Birkenau and Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everybody looks at her, that she has lost her mind.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody would believe.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It came to such a point that the people were telling her-- she used to be-- not like a maid, but like a helping hand to somebody's house.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she was trying to put the whole effort to explain to these people who knew her about what's going on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They thought that-- she, or their family, of course, would believe her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they wouldn't believe her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it came to a point where they told her that if she doesn't stop spreading around such false rumors, that they will take her and lock her up, and put her in a psychiatric hospital.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When she talks to me, I look in bewilderment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What are you talking about?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is true?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But you can see from this, on the inhumanity that they were subjecting people to, that a normal thinking human being would never believe that this can happen-- with mass graves, mass gassing.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she says, she escaped to Hungary, because she was afraid that her fellow Jews would commit her to a sanitarium-- to an asylum.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She escaped to Hungary, and there she lived in safety until 1944.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And now she came back with the Hungarian transport for the second time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She says that if the Nazis find that out, she'd be put to death in a second, because there is no bigger sin by the Nazis to escape a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she says, I cannot live with the thought by myself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have to share it with somebody.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
